

TAHAK

   This is not that common a word.

   tahak
   to take a shortcut

   The following conjugation is more often used:
   tahakin
   to go on a challenging path

   tahakin ang landas
   to take the difficult path

   Tahakin ang landas patungo sa kuweba.
   Take the difficult path to the cave.

   future tense: tatahakin

   ang landas na tinahak
   the path taken

   ang landas na tinahak ko
   the path that I took

   Sabay nating itahak ang daan ito.
   Let’s go on this path together.

   ang pagtahak
   the act of exploring,
   taking on a new path

   ang pagtahak ng sariling landas
   charting one’s own path

   matahak

   Kahulugan ng “pagtahak” sa Tagalog: paglakad sa landas, bagtas,
   balagtas

   tahakin = landasin, daanan
